data.title: Phymorhynchus moskalevi
data.text:
Species of gastropod

Phymorhynchus moskalevi Scientific classification Domain: Eukaryota Kingdom: Animalia Phylum: Mollusca Class: Gastropoda Subclass: Caenogastropoda Order: Neogastropoda Superfamily: Conoidea Family: Raphitomidae Genus: Phymorhynchus Species:

P. moskalevi

Binomial name Phymorhynchus moskalevi

Sysoev & Kantor, 1995[1]

Phymorhynchus moskalevi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae.[2]

This species has been described from hydrothermal vents in 1995.[1]

Description

[edit]

The length of the shell attains 39 mm.

Distribution

[edit]

This species occurs on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge.
